# Component Library

Before building UI, check **`packages/app/src/lib/components`** (`$lib/components`). Prefer existing primitives and domain components over duplicating markup or behavior.

## Reuse First

| Layer      | Path                                            | Use for                         |
| ---------- | ----------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| Primitives | `ui/` — Button, Dialog, Popover, Tabs, Input, … | Generic, styled building blocks |
| Domain     | `match/`, `player/`, `lobby/`, `replay/`, …     | Feature-specific but shared UI  |
| Widgets    | `widgets/`                                      | Dashboard / status surfaces     |

Import from barrel `index.ts` files when available. Extend an existing component with props or snippets before copying its markup.

## When to Extract

Create or generalize a component when the same UI appears in **2+ places**, or when a single place needs a **clear, testable boundary** (context, variants, composition). Keep one-off layout inline in routes — do not over-abstract.

## New Component Checklist

Match existing patterns in this repo:

1. **Svelte 5 runes** — `$props()`, `$derived`, `{#snippet}` / `{@render}` (see `svelte-patterns.mdc`)
2. **bits-ui** for interactive primitives — Dialog, Popover, Tabs, Select, etc.; style with `cn()` and project tokens
3. **runed** for shared state — `Context` + `createX` / `useX` for component trees; `watch` for side effects in `.svelte.ts` modules
4. **Types** — export `XxxProps` from `index.ts`; spread `...restProps` onto the root element
5. **Barrel export** — `index.ts` re-exports public API; keep implementation files co-located

```typescript
// context.ts — scoped data for a component family
import { Context } from 'runed';

const context = new Context<() => Match>('<match />');
export const createMatch = (match: () => Match) => context.set(match);
export const useMatch = () => context.get()();
```

```svelte
<!-- ui/example/example.svelte — bits-ui + snippets -->
<script lang="ts">
	import { Popover, type WithoutChildren } from 'bits-ui';
	import { cn } from '$lib/utils';
	import type { Snippet } from 'svelte';

	type Props = { trigger: Snippet; children: Snippet } & WithoutChildren<Popover.RootProps>;
	let { trigger, children, ...restProps }: Props = $props();
</script>

<Popover.Root {...restProps}>
	<!-- compose primitives; style with cn() -->
</Popover.Root>
```

Place new files in the folder that matches scope: generic → `ui/`, feature-specific → the feature folder (e.g. `match/`).
